{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XcBvH7TaVN5xGtGY1C7bKc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.net.URI;\n     4→\n     5→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     6→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    18→\n    19→@Path(\"/owners/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/visits\")\n    20→public class VisitResource {\n    21→\n    22→\t@Inject\n    23→\tOwnerRepository owners;\n    24→\n    25→\t@Inject\n    26→\tTemplate createOrUpdateVisitForm;\n    27→\n    28→\t@GET\n    29→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n    30→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    31→\tpublic TemplateInstance initNewVisitForm(\n    32→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    33→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId) {\n    34→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    35→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    36→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    37→\t\tVisit visit = new Visit();\n    38→\t\treturn createOrUpdateVisitForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n    39→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    40→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    41→\t\t\t\t.data(\"visit\", visit);\n    42→\t}\n    43→\n    44→\t@POST\n    45→\t@Path(\"/new\")\n    46→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    47→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    48→\t@Transactional\n    49→\tpublic Object processNewVisitForm(\n    50→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    51→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId,\n    52→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"date\") String dateStr,\n    53→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"description\") String description) {\n    54→\n    55→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    56→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    57→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    58→\n    59→\t\tVisit visit = new Visit();\n    60→\t\tif (dateStr != null && !dateStr.isBlank()) {\n    61→\t\t\tvisit.setDate(java.time.LocalDate.parse(dateStr));\n    62→\t\t}\n    63→\t\tvisit.setDescription(description);\n    64→\n    65→\t\t// Validation\n    66→\t\tif (description == null || description.isBlank()) {\n    67→\t\t\treturn createOrUpdateVisitForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n    68→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    69→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    70→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"visit\", visit)\n    71→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"error\", \"Description is required.\");\n    72→\t\t}\n    73→\n    74→\t\towner.addVisit(petId, visit);\n    75→\t\towners.save(owner);\n    76→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n    77→\t}\n    78→\n    79→}\n    80→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"cfbd750e-984c-414e-abf1-5172f15726cd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mbqj8vddgDCJnKcpydiWnn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     6→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.DefaultValue;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→\n    15→@Path(\"/\")\n    16→public class VetResource {\n    17→\n    18→\t@Inject\n    19→\tVetRepository vetRepository;\n    20→\n    21→\t@Inject\n    22→\tTemplate vetList;\n    23→\n    24→\t@GET\n    25→\t@Path(\"/vets.html\")\n    26→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    27→\tpublic TemplateInstance showVetList(@QueryParam(\"page\") @DefaultValue(\"1\") int page) {\n    28→\t\tint pageSize = 5;\n    29→\t\tList<Vet> listVets = vetRepository.findAll(page, pageSize);\n    30→\t\tlong totalItems = vetRepository.count();\n    31→\t\tint totalPages = (int) Math.ceil((double) totalItems / pageSize);\n    32→\n    33→\t\treturn vetList.data(\"menu\", \"vets\")\n    34→\t\t\t\t.data(\"listVets\", listVets)\n    35→\t\t\t\t.data(\"currentPage\", page)\n    36→\t\t\t\t.data(\"totalPages\", totalPages)\n    37→\t\t\t\t.data(\"totalItems\", totalItems);\n    38→\t}\n    39→\n    40→\t@GET\n    41→\t@Path(\"/vets\")\n    42→\t@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    43→\tpublic Vets showResourcesVetList() {\n    44→\t\tVets vets = new Vets();\n    45→\t\tvets.getVetList().addAll(vetRepository.findAll());\n    46→\t\treturn vets;\n    47→\t}\n    48→\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"ca3955e6-e764-46c2-9285-04f5bc5ee467"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Eraf54sz5XyGxeaEL7btgg","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     4→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    10→\n    11→@Path(\"/\")\n    12→public class WelcomeResource {\n    13→\n    14→\t@Inject\n    15→\tTemplate welcome;\n    16→\n    17→\t@GET\n    18→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    19→\tpublic TemplateInstance welcome() {\n    20→\t\treturn welcome.data(\"menu\", \"home\");\n    21→\t}\n    22→\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"063b352f-f62b-4d45-9e5f-051c2b477ca0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WZH5d6vXZc6iyf36TLhJKK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     7→\n     8→@Path(\"/oups\")\n     9→public class CrashResource {\n    10→\n    11→\t@GET\n    12→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    13→\tpublic String triggerException() {\n    14→\t\tthrow new RuntimeException(\n    15→\t\t\t\t\"Expected: controller used to showcase what happens when an exception is thrown\");\n    16→\t}\n    17→\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"cea7df09-1ff3-41dd-a2af-5e746d494a1d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01GEJqSeaHRaydokzZvxY3QE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I can see the issue clearly. The route conflict is:\n\n- `OwnerResource`: `@Path(\"/owners\")` class-level, with `@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}\")` on `showOwner()` method → resolves to `/owners/1`\n- `PetResource`: `@Path(\"/owners/{ownerId: [0-9]+}\")` class-level → also matches `/owners/1` at the class level\n\nWhen RESTEasy sees `/owners/1`, it may match PetResource's class-level path first, then find no matching sub-resource method (since PetResource methods are at `/pets/new` or `/pets/{petId}/edit`), resulting in a 404.\n\nThe fix is to change PetResource to use `/owners` as the class-level path and include the full `/{ownerId}/pets/...` in method paths, similar to OwnerResource. Let me fix this:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2927,"cache_read_input_tokens":28140,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2927,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":413},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"3c0a1d23-af5b-4037-a662-cfc304ccbb16"}
