{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01D697tbQhoW512TAaXAYDJr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.net.URI;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.util.Collection;\n     6→\n     7→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     8→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    19→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    20→\n    21→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    22→public class PetResource {\n    23→\n    24→\t@Inject\n    25→\tOwnerRepository owners;\n    26→\n    27→\t@Inject\n    28→\tPetTypeRepository types;\n    29→\n    30→\t@Inject\n    31→\tTemplate createOrUpdatePetForm;\n    32→\n    33→\t@GET\n    34→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/new\")\n    35→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    36→\tpublic TemplateInstance initCreationForm(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId) {\n    37→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    38→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    39→\t\tCollection<PetType> petTypes = types.findPetTypes();\n    40→\t\tPet pet = new Pet();\n    41→\t\treturn createOrUpdatePetForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n    42→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    43→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    44→\t\t\t\t.data(\"types\", petTypes)\n    45→\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", true);\n    46→\t}\n    47→\n    48→\t@POST\n    49→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/new\")\n    50→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    51→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    52→\t@Transactional\n    53→\tpublic Object processCreationForm(\n    54→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    55→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"name\") String name,\n    56→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"birthDate\") String birthDateStr,\n    57→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"type\") String typeName) {\n    58→\n    59→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    60→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    61→\n    62→\t\tPet pet = new Pet();\n    63→\t\tpet.setName(name);\n    64→\n    65→\t\tif (birthDateStr != null && !birthDateStr.isBlank()) {\n    66→\t\t\tpet.setBirthDate(LocalDate.parse(birthDateStr));\n    67→\t\t}\n    68→\n    69→\t\tif (typeName != null && !typeName.isBlank()) {\n    70→\t\t\tPetType petType = types.findByName(typeName);\n    71→\t\t\tpet.setType(petType);\n    72→\t\t}\n    73→\n    74→\t\t// Validation\n    75→\t\tCollection<PetType> petTypes = types.findPetTypes();\n    76→\t\tif (name == null || name.isBlank() || pet.getType() == null || pet.getBirthDate() == null) {\n    77→\t\t\treturn createOrUpdatePetForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n    78→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    79→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    80→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"types\", petTypes)\n    81→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", true)\n    82→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"error\", \"Please fill all required fields.\");\n    83→\t\t}\n    84→\n    85→\t\towner.addPet(pet);\n    86→\t\towners.save(owner);\n    87→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n    88→\t}\n    89→\n    90→\t@GET\n    91→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/edit\")\n    92→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    93→\tpublic TemplateInstance initUpdateForm(\n    94→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    95→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId) {\n    96→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    97→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    98→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    99→\t\tCollection<PetType> petTypes = types.findPetTypes();\n   100→\t\treturn createOrUpdatePetForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n   101→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n   102→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n   103→\t\t\t\t.data(\"types\", petTypes)\n   104→\t\t\t\t.data(\"isNew\", false);\n   105→\t}\n   106→\n   107→\t@POST\n   108→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/edit\")\n   109→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   110→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   111→\t@Transactional\n   112→\tpublic Object processUpdateForm(\n   113→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n   114→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId,\n   115→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"name\") String name,\n   116→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"birthDate\") String birthDateStr,\n   117→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"type\") String typeName) {\n   118→\n   119→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n   120→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n   121→\n   122→\t\tPet existingPet = owner.getPet(petId);\n   123→\n   124→\t\tif (existingPet != null) {\n   125→\t\t\texistingPet.setName(name);\n   126→\t\t\tif (birthDateStr != null && !birthDateStr.isBlank()) {\n   127→\t\t\t\texistingPet.setBirthDate(LocalDate.parse(birthDateStr));\n   128→\t\t\t}\n   129→\t\t\tif (typeName != null && !typeName.isBlank()) {\n   130→\t\t\t\tPetType petType = types.findByName(typeName);\n   131→\t\t\t\texistingPet.setType(petType);\n   132→\t\t\t}\n   133→\t\t}\n   134→\n   135→\t\towners.save(owner);\n   136→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n   137→\t}\n   138→\n   139→}\n   140→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"252d9b56-98d1-45b2-aed4-1e03e5178d73"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UCJYHmX3tw9twXpVzxuLCy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.net.URI;\n     4→\n     5→import io.quarkus.qute.Template;\n     6→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    18→\n    19→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    20→public class VisitResource {\n    21→\n    22→\t@Inject\n    23→\tOwnerRepository owners;\n    24→\n    25→\t@Inject\n    26→\tTemplate createOrUpdateVisitForm;\n    27→\n    28→\t@GET\n    29→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/visits/new\")\n    30→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    31→\tpublic TemplateInstance initNewVisitForm(\n    32→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    33→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId) {\n    34→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    35→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    36→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    37→\t\tVisit visit = new Visit();\n    38→\t\treturn createOrUpdateVisitForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n    39→\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    40→\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    41→\t\t\t\t.data(\"visit\", visit);\n    42→\t}\n    43→\n    44→\t@POST\n    45→\t@Path(\"/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/visits/new\")\n    46→\t@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    47→\t@Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    48→\t@Transactional\n    49→\tpublic Object processNewVisitForm(\n    50→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"ownerId\") int ownerId,\n    51→\t\t\t@PathParam(\"petId\") int petId,\n    52→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"date\") String dateStr,\n    53→\t\t\t@FormParam(\"description\") String description) {\n    54→\n    55→\t\tOwner owner = owners.findById(ownerId)\n    56→\t\t\t\t.orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(\"Owner not found with id: \" + ownerId));\n    57→\t\tPet pet = owner.getPet(petId);\n    58→\n    59→\t\tVisit visit = new Visit();\n    60→\t\tif (dateStr != null && !dateStr.isBlank()) {\n    61→\t\t\tvisit.setDate(java.time.LocalDate.parse(dateStr));\n    62→\t\t}\n    63→\t\tvisit.setDescription(description);\n    64→\n    65→\t\t// Validation\n    66→\t\tif (description == null || description.isBlank()) {\n    67→\t\t\treturn createOrUpdateVisitForm.data(\"menu\", \"owners\")\n    68→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"owner\", owner)\n    69→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"pet\", pet)\n    70→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"visit\", visit)\n    71→\t\t\t\t\t.data(\"error\", \"Description is required.\");\n    72→\t\t}\n    73→\n    74→\t\towner.addVisit(petId, visit);\n    75→\t\towners.save(owner);\n    76→\t\treturn Response.seeOther(URI.create(\"/owners/\" + ownerId)).build();\n    77→\t}\n    78→\n    79→}\n    80→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"3b2ff5ab-7290-4d7d-9c88-32e794c8d767"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01L6EhVpFbidKXRPzeRhUNjZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The routes now look correct. All three resources use `@Path(\"/owners\")` at the class level, and the method-level paths differentiate properly:\n\n- `OwnerResource`: `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}`, `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/edit`, `/new`, `/find`\n- `PetResource`: `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/new`, `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/edit`\n- `VisitResource`: `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/visits/new`\n\nNo overlapping class-level paths that could cause ambiguity. Now let me rebuild the Docker image and test:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3684,"cache_read_input_tokens":35042,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3684,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":618},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"c7a8de6b-a987-48c2-a3aa-1c52b3fdfe6c"}
