{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013TNtQscYQmQVuez3mvo6FL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.springframework.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import java.util.Optional;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    10→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Repository class for Owner domain objects.\n    14→ */\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class OwnerRepository {\n    17→\n    18→\t@Inject\n    19→\tEntityManager em;\n    20→\n    21→\tpublic Optional<Owner> findById(Integer id) {\n    22→\t\tOwner owner = em.find(Owner.class, id);\n    23→\t\treturn Optional.ofNullable(owner);\n    24→\t}\n    25→\n    26→\tpublic List<Owner> findByLastNameStartingWith(String lastName, int page, int pageSize) {\n    27→\t\tTypedQuery<Owner> query = em.createQuery(\n    28→\t\t\t\t\"SELECT o FROM Owner o WHERE LOWER(o.lastName) LIKE LOWER(:lastName) ORDER BY o.lastName\",\n    29→\t\t\t\tOwner.class);\n    30→\t\tquery.setParameter(\"lastName\", lastName + \"%\");\n    31→\t\tquery.setFirstResult((page - 1) * pageSize);\n    32→\t\tquery.setMaxResults(pageSize);\n    33→\t\treturn query.getResultList();\n    34→\t}\n    35→\n    36→\tpublic long countByLastNameStartingWith(String lastName) {\n    37→\t\tTypedQuery<Long> query = em.createQuery(\n    38→\t\t\t\t\"SELECT COUNT(o) FROM Owner o WHERE LOWER(o.lastName) LIKE LOWER(:lastName)\",\n    39→\t\t\t\tLong.class);\n    40→\t\tquery.setParameter(\"lastName\", lastName + \"%\");\n    41→\t\treturn query.getSingleResult();\n    42→\t}\n    43→\n    44→\t@Transactional\n    45→\tpublic Owner save(Owner owner) {\n    46→\t\tif (owner.isNew()) {\n    47→\t\t\tem.persist(owner);\n    48→\t\t\treturn owner;\n    49→\t\t} else {\n    50→\t\t\treturn em.merge(owner);\n    51→\t\t}\n    52→\t}\n    53→\n    54→}\n    55→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"cfc80c54-c234-45c4-ae87-dfbd6890be08"}
