{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UKA6qSCF4fdaUfYvvGA1Qp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Spring Boot to Quarkus migration is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished in this continuation:\n\n**Issues fixed:**\n\n1. **Route conflict causing `/owners/1` 404**: The `PetResource` class-level `@Path(\"/owners/{ownerId: [0-9]+}\")` was consuming requests intended for `OwnerResource`. Fixed by changing both `PetResource` and `VisitResource` to use `@Path(\"/owners\")` at the class level, with `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/...` and `/{ownerId: [0-9]+}/pets/{petId: [0-9]+}/visits/...` at the method level.\n\n2. **H2 identity counter conflict causing 500 on owner creation**: The `import.sql` seed data used explicit IDs (1-13) but H2's auto-increment counter wasn't advanced past them. Fixed by adding `ALTER TABLE ... ALTER COLUMN id RESTART WITH 100` for all tables.\n\n**Final test results:** All 8 smoke tests pass (welcome page, find owners, owners list, owner details, vets HTML, vets JSON, create owner, static resources).\n\n**Files modified in this session:**\n- `PetResource.java` - Fixed class-level path and method-level paths\n- `VisitResource.java` - Fixed class-level path and method-level paths\n- `import.sql` - Added identity counter reset statements\n- `CHANGELOG.md` - Created with full migration documentation"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":506,"cache_read_input_tokens":66616,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":506,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":350},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"989b6ec8-5330-484b-9e5f-c61fa819ffe2","uuid":"dc2597d4-0224-4c01-92dc-32de2ab72170"}
